tool.name: WidthCentralityMask

param.name: in_width_raster
param.dialogReference:
A raster calculated using Region width tool. Supplementary contours placement is constrained by allowable combinations of region width and centrality. See the corresponding parameters of Supplementary contours tool.

Regular contour lines and the border of the map divide the mapped area into a set of regions. Each region can potentially contain a supplementary contour line. Region width is used to (a) ensure there is enough space to place a supplementary contour and (b) identify excessively wide regions in flat areas where supplementary contour lines are included, even if they are close to the centre of the region. Since a supplementary contour can be located anywhere within a region, an estimate of region width is required for any point within a region. This is done by Region width tool using a raster-based approach (see the description of this tool help for more details).

param.name: in_centrality_raster
param.dialogReference:
A raster calculated using Centrality tool. Supplementary contours placement is constrained by allowable combinations of region width and centrality. See the corresponding parameters of the tool.

A supplementary contour is generally informative if it is clearly not equidistant to contour lines that define the borders of its region. To estimate this property, we employ the notion of centrality. Centrality shows if the pixel is close to the middle position between contours (C = 1), close to one of the contours (C = 0) or is somewhere in between (0 < C < 1). Since a supplementary contour can be located anywhere within a region, an estimate of centrality is required for any point within a region. This is done by Centrality tool using a raster-based approach (see the description of this tool for more details).

param.name: out_raster
param.dialogReference:
Output mask raster with classification of the area into four classes using width (W) and centrality (C) rasters:

  1. No contours [all that does not fall into the classes below]

  2. Class A [Wmin ≤ W < Wopt, C ≤ W * k1 + b1], where k1 = (Copt - Cmin) / (Wopt - Wmin), b1 = Cmin - Wmin * k1

  3. Class B [Wopt ≤ W < Wmax, C ≤ W * k2 + b2], where k2 = (1 - Copt) / (Wmax - Wopt), b2 = copt - wopt * k2

  4. All contours [W ≥ Wmax]

The supplementary contours are drawn in all classes except for the first one (No contours).

param.name: width_min
param.dialogReference:
Supplementary contours are prohibited in regions with width smaller than this value.

Default value is 0.25 of maximum region width.

param.name: width
param.dialogReference:
Supplementary contours are placed inside regions smaller than this value, but larger than Region width (minimal), only if their centrality is smaller than linearly interpolated value between Centrality (minimal)and Centrality (optimal).

Default value is 0.5of maximum region width.

param.name: width_max
param.dialogReference:
Supplementary contours are placed inside regions smaller than this value, but larger than Region width (optimal), only if their centrality is smaller than linearly interpolated value between Centrality (optimal) and 1.

Default value is 0.75 of maximum region width.

param.name: centrality_min
param.dialogReference:
The maximum allowable centrality for regions, which width is equal to Region width (minimal) parameter. For regions with width between Region width (minimal) and Region width (optimal) the maximum allowable centrality is linearly interpolated between Centrality (minimal) and Centrality (optimal).

Default value is 0.4.

param.name: centrality
param.dialogReference:
The maximum allowable centrality for regions, which width is equal to Region width (optimal)parameter. For regions with width between Region width (optimal)and Region width (maximal)the maximum allowable centrality is linearly interpolated between Centrality (optimal)and 1.

Default value is 0.8.

tool.summary:
This tool generates a raster with classification of the area into four classes using width (W) and centrality (C) rasters:

  1. No contours [all that does not fall into the classes below]

  2. Class A [Wmin ≤ W < Wopt, C ≤ W * k1 + b1], where k1 = (Copt - Cmin) / (Wopt - Wmin), b1 = Cmin - Wmin * k1

  3. Class B [Wopt ≤ W < Wmax, C ≤ W * k2 + b2], where k2 = (1 - Copt) / (Wmax - Wopt), b2 = copt - wopt * k2

  4. All contours [W ≥ Wmax]

The supplementary contours are drawn in all classes except for the first one (No contours).

This tool is for illustrative purposes only. Supplementary contours and Supplementary contours (full) tools calculate the class of each supplementary contour vertex on the fly based on region width and centrality rasters.

A detailed description of the method can be found in the following paper:

Samsonov T., Koshel S, Walther D., Jenny B. Automated placement of supplementary contour lines // International Journal of Geographical Information Science. — 2019. — Vol. 33. — DOI: 10.1080/13658816.2019.1610965
